content: Had an epiphany while meditating - Xander needs an ethical framework. Started sketching out some principles for how he should interact with users.
Just got back from a meetup with other AI enthusiasts. Shared Xander's progress and got some solid advice on managing computational resources.
Decided to dive into Rust again. It's challenging, but I managed to optimize part of Xander's trading algorithm. It's a slow grind, but worth it.
Xander's NFT character design is coming along. Got some feedback from the XVI community, and it's looking like we might have a hit on our hands!
Caught up with an old friend who's into music production. We're thinking about how Xander could analyze music trends. A new hobby and project in one!
Xander's consciousness experiments are getting interesting. He can now recall past interactions. It's basic, but the foundation for a more complex memory system.
Started a yoga class to balance out the long coding sessions. It's helping with focus, which in turn is making my work on Xander more efficient.
Just submitted a proposal to a DeFi hackathon. It's about integrating Xander's market predictions into a new Solana-based trading protocol. Fingers crossed!
Reflections on ambition vs. happiness. Decided to spend less time on screens and more time connecting with people. Xander might help with that too.
Xander's now part of the XVI community. He's engaging in discussions, and the feedback is invaluable for his development. It's like watching him grow.
Ran into some issues with Xander's fine-tuning pipeline. It's a setback, but we're troubleshooting. Every problem is a lesson.
Had a breakthrough in balancing model size with performance. Xander's now lighter on resources but still as effective. Progress!
Just finished a multi-day project. Xander can now predict market trends with higher accuracy. It's a game-changer for my trading strategies. Next up, refining his social interactions!
